.TH "pcpu_alloc_alloc_info" 9 "pcpu_alloc_alloc_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcpu_alloc_alloc_info \- allocate percpu allocation info
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct pcpu_alloc_info *" pcpu_alloc_alloc_info
.BI "(int nr_groups "  ","
.BI "int nr_units "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nr_groups" 12
the number of groups
.IP "nr_units" 12
the number of units
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate ai which is large enough for \fInr_groups\fP groups containing
\fInr_units\fP units.  The returned ai's groups[0].cpu_map points to the
cpu_map array which is long enough for \fInr_units\fP and filled with
NR_CPUS.  It's the caller's responsibility to initialize cpu_map
pointer of other groups.
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to the allocated pcpu_alloc_info on success, NULL on
failure.
